This paper belongs to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with the study of malicious hacking products and their categorization. Additionally, it may also fall under the sub-category of cybercrime (cs.CY) as it deals with illegal activities on the darkweb and deepweb. The paper also involves data analysis and clustering techniques (cs.SE) to understand the various categories of products. It may also fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as the authors have collected information from multiple sources and created a unified database schema. Finally, the paper involves data mining techniques (cs.DS) to extract insights from the collected data.
